  "text": "This appendix will delineate the analytic and conceptual relations between demographic entropy, the parameter used in this study, and thermodynamic entropy, a notion that is sometimes invoked in heuristic models of aging. The concepts demographic entropy and thermodynamic entropy have their origin in evolutionary theory and thermodynamic theory, respectively. Both theories have similar mathematical structures, and involve concepts that are analytically related when evaluated at the cellular level of biological organization. A detailed account of the analytic relationship between the two theories is described in Demetrius [CITATION_1] .",
